Am I addicted to porn?
-----------------------------
"Suddenly i like watching porn, i know it's wrong but i enjoy it since i haven't had sex yet. How do i stop?"
 -----------------------------
It's natural to be curious about sex and your body. For many young people porn can be a way to satisfy that curiosity. You're brave for speaking up and asking for help there is nothing to be ashamed of! ü§óBut if you are watching it a lot, porn can be very harmful. 
It's important to understand that porn is not real sex, so it can set up the wrong expectations about what sexual relationships are supposed to look like. 
This can affect your relationships and hold you back from having a healthy sex life in the future. 
Porn can also be very addictive, especially if you're not sure how to handle the feelings that it comes with. Talk to someone you trust. This can be a friend, a parent or an auntie. You can also type Help in this chat, we can link you up to a confidential emergency helpline.

I want to stay a virgin but I feel pressured to have sex. 
-----------------------------
"I'm a virgin,I want to stay that way till I'm married but sometimes I feel like I want to have sex (weary face) and that I'm missing out on the fun"
 -----------------------------
The decision to have sex is very personal. First up, I want you to know that it's 100% natural to be interested in sex. During adolescence, your hormones will spark lots of new feelings including varying levels of sexual desire. Whether you act on these feelings or not is your choice.
I understand there might be pressure to engage in sexual activity. It can often feel like everyone's doing it. But remember ur feelings and experiences will be different from your friends! U have to go with how u feel at the time and what is right for you. 
If you want to wait, that's 100% ur decision, and that's awesome! If you feel ready, make sure you think about what you are comfortable with and remember to use contraception. No matter what you decide sex isn't going anywhere, it will always be there when you and your future partner are ready. ü§ó

Seeing double
-----------------------------
"Is it normal to love two guys at the same time?"
 -----------------------------
Yes, it is normal to like two people at once and this can be confusing. The emotions you feel may be difficult to understand, so you should try to be respectful and honest with everyone involved, even with yourself.
Though your heart may be torn, you will have to make a decision. Think hard about why you like each of them, how they treat you and how you feel when you're with them. While you're deciding maybe pull back from both guys and focus on being friends and see where that goes. 
Getting to know them as friends will lower the pressure of the situation and you can still have fun together. Once you're ready then you can move towards something more serious, more wisely, having carefully weighed up your options. Even better having not been hurtful or dishonest with either guy.

I know about cum but what's pre-cum? 
-----------------------------
"What is pre-cum?"
 -----------------------------
Before an orgasm, the penis releases a liquid called pre-ejaculant, which has sperm cells. When sperm from a penis meets and egg in a woman's uterus (also known as her womb) during sexual activity, this is called fertilisation. A fertilised egg can implant in the womb lining and a baby can grow, resulting in pregnancy. Because pre-cum has sperm cells in it, this is enough to make you fall pregnant if you are not using any form of contraception. 
The best way to make sure that you won't fall pregnant is to use a condom or other contraceptives. There are load of different types of hormonal ones such as the pill, IUS or the vaginal ring. You can visit a doctor or a local clinic to discuss the best options for you! ü§ó
Remember that a condom is the only method that helps protect from STI transmission. Sex is much more enjoyable when you do it safely as you don't need to worry. For more advice you can also contact Love Life on 011 523 1000, it's a toll-free line.

He's a cheater. Should I care?
-----------------------------
"The guy I'm having sex with has a girlfriend. Is it okay to keep on having sex with him because its so amazing and i don't have feelings for him?"
 -----------------------------
Mhm, this is a tough one. Firstly, having sex with someone who has multiple partners increases the chances of STI transmission, so it's really important to use condoms in order to enjoy sex safely. Secondly, sexual activity can stimulate feelings between partners, so it's important to reflect on how you feel and if your feelings start to change at all.
You may not want want to have a relationship with this person, but when you have sex with someone you are essentially entrusting them with your body and health.
Think deeply about the pros and cons of your decision. ‚òÇÔ∏è. If you do decided to keep seeing them, make sure to use condoms every time. Regardless of whether you're in a relationship or not, you deserve respect.

"What's the right age to have sex?"
 -----------------------------
People decide to start having sex at different ages for different reasons. So it's not easy to give you an exact age. Some people are guided by their religion or their culture. And others are guided by their own feelings and beliefs.
But one thing is for sure for all of us- when having sex it's important to be responsible about it. This means making smart and safe sex choices, like using contraception every time you have sex or waiting until you and your partner both feel ready. üíï
It's important that it's your decision, based on your values, and that you and the other person both say "yes" to it. ü§ó Not everyone matures at the same rate or feels ready at the same time. The right time to have sex is when you feel ready to learn about safer sex.

If you decide to go ahead, we can talk about your contraception options whenever you want.  When it comes to your body, health and wellbeing, you're in the driver's seatüíñ.

I can also give you the deets of a friendly service who can get you sorted with the right contraception 4 u, if you want?
Can someone tell if you've had sex before?
-----------------------------
"Can a guy actually tell if I slept with someone other than him? Can he feel it?"
 -----------------------------
I get asked this question all the time. Fun fact: there‚Äôs absolutely no way for someone to be able to tell if you have had sex before. You see, virginity is just a concept, there is no scientific test of evidence to be able to check it. Your vagina won‚Äôt feel different after having sex for the first time. What‚Äôs cool about vaginas is that they are elastic which means they expand during sex but then go back to their normal size soon after sex. 
But what about the hymen? I'm gonna be real with you. The 'hymen' is actually referring to a vaginal corona, which is the wall lining at the entrance to the vagina. Everyone's is different it could be thick or thin, and sometimes has little tears in already, which might cause slight bleeding. It can tear any time in your life. That includes exercising, going for a run, or just your body growing! It has no relation to whether you've had sex before or not. It's just a myth. A stupid one at that. üòâ
If someone is pressuring you to "prove" your virginity, have a think if they're really the right person for you. You have the right to choose if, how and when you might engage in sexual activity. This means it is your decision, made by you and you only. If you decide to be sexually active, make sure it's on your terms. Remember to always use contraception in order to enjoy safe sex. üòÑ

Pregnant and on your periodüò≤
-----------------------------
"Can I get pregnant if I have unprotected sex while on my period"
 -----------------------------
Yes, it is still possible to get pregnant during that time. How? Well, sperm can live for up to 5 days inside you. So if you have unprotected sex during your period, that sperm still has a chance of fertilizing one of your eggs that are released during ovulation.
Ovulation happens in the middle of menstruation. You're very fertile a day or 2 either side an egg being released, this is also called ovulation. If you start ovulating a few days before having unprotected period sex, your egg could meet with his sperm - and you might get pregnant.
Having unprotected sex while on your period will also put you at risk for HIV or STI infection or infecting the person you‚Äôre sleeping with. My advice is to always play it safe ‚Äì use a condom every time. That way you won't have to worry pregnancy or an infection.

Am I pregnant? 
-----------------------------
"When can you tell that you're pregnant?"
 -----------------------------
Usually, the first sign of pregnancy is a missed period. Some people will also experience morning sickness like vomiting or not wanting to eat certain foods. But you can‚Äôt only rely on these signs. The best way to know for sure is to have a pregnancy test done.
If you get tested by a nurse or doctor, they will ask you some questions like when was your last period before testing you for pregnancy. And if the test comes back positive ‚Äì that you are pregnant ‚Äì you will be advised on how to take care of yourself during the pregnancy. 
There is also the option of buying a home-pregnancy test from shops like Clicks or the pharmacy. These tests are usually reliable but you will still need to see a nurse or doctor so that they can help you have a healthy and safe pregnancy and talk to you about your options. 

If you like, I can give you the deets of a Big Sis-approved health service where you can get a pregnancy test and discuss your options, including for termination if that's what you want?
Transfering HIV 
-----------------------------
"Is HIV easily transferred "
 -----------------------------
HIV is a virus that attacks a person's immune system. HIV lives in a person's bodily fluids such as blood, semen and vaginal fluids.  It can be transferred through a few different ways, such as from birth or sharing unsterlised needles. The most common way is via sexual activity including oral, vaginal and anal sex. 
There are lots of ways you can minimise the chances of HIV transmission such as always using a condom during sex. You can also try using PrEP, which is medication you can take to prevent transmission. You will need to visit a health clinic to get more information on this.  If you have sex with someone who is HIV+ without using a condom or PrEP,  there is a chance of HIV transmission. 
If you ever feel like you may have been exposed to HIV, it's a good idea to take a visit to your local clinic and try an HIV test. It's a really easy test, it's a tiny finger prick of blood. Knowing your status is a responsible thing to do so you can make informed choices for your sexual health and wellbeing.

If you need more information, you can call the LoveLife helpline for free on: 011 523 1000 
My partner wants to have sex with multiple people 
-----------------------------
"I've decided to finally have sex with my boyfriend but he told me that he will be having sex with other girls too so should I go through with it?"
 -----------------------------
It sounds like you've been taking the time to think things through and consider what feels right for you. So, good on you for wanting to be responsible  üòÄ  It seems like you and your partner might want different things in your relationship. 
Having sex with someone who has multiple partners does increase the chances of STI transmission including HIV. You're responsible for your own sexual health, so it's important to always use a condom during sexual activity so as to ensure you're enjoying sex safely.
Think about how you feel emotionally, and if it might hurt to see your partner with other girls. Talk to someone you trust about this, they can help you weigh these risks.You need to decide what is best for you. It wouldn‚Äôt be fair on you to compromise your values just to make your partner happy so make sure your final decision stays true to you. ü§ó

Unsure about masturbation 
-----------------------------
"Is masturbating good?"
 -----------------------------
Thinking about sex might lead to exploring your bodies in new ways. Sometimes, this might lead to masturbation. üìñMasturbation is touching or stroking oneself, especially genitals, for sexual pleasure.
Masturbation is not something we should be ashamed of. It's normal for us to have these body curiosities.
Some people may feel guilty for masturbating, as they think it's wrong. Others might be scared  if they've heard myths that masturbation leads to illness. This can make it extra confusing! Well, let me tell you that masturbation is neither physically or mentally harmful. It's actually a cool way to understand your body. ü§ó
What matters is how you feel when doing it and that you have privacy and safety to explore your body as you wish. However you feel about it, the only important thing is that you feel comfortable. You body = always your decision.

How to support a friend having relationship issues 
-----------------------------
"My friend is being cheated on. What can I say to comfort her?"
 -----------------------------
Eish‚Ä¶finding out that your friend is being cheated on sucks. It makes me happy, though, that you care so much about your friend. We girls need to always support each other üòé. You can help her get through this time by letting her know that what he did is not her fault. 
Being cheated on can make someone feel insecure or become distrusting. Remind her that she is still an amazing person. During this time, it is important for her to know that she is not alone ‚Äì listening to her and giving her a safe space to share her feelings can help her heal. 
Check in on her often, whether it‚Äôs through WhatsApp or inviting her over for a sleep over.  You can also talk to her about her future goals ‚Äì this will be a good way to remind her that she still has a lot of good things to look forward to.

Does love really exist? 
-----------------------------
"What's the meaning of love and how came I fall in love? "
 -----------------------------
Wow girl that is deep question üòÖ. Love is an emotion that we feel for people who are close to us. We then act out that love in different ways like caring for them, respecting them and being loyal and kind to them
Love between two people can happen in different ways. Sometimes it can start off as a crush. Other times it grows from a friendship. Love doesn‚Äôt happen overnight, it takes time, patience and understanding. üíïFeeling love for a someone is something many girls go through and it‚Äôs normal. üòÄ
You probably fell in love with someone that you admire and vibe with. Sometimes we can confuse love for infatuation. Infatuation is usually a short lived feeling of excitement based on physical attraction. But love happens in its own time - so try not to be hard on yourself or overthink it. ü§ó

I want my ex back 
-----------------------------
"How can I go about talking to an ex I hurt??"
 -----------------------------
Rebuilding a friendship with someone you hurt can be really tricky. They may have moved on and want nothing to do with you. Or speaking to you might still cause them pain üíî. If you haven‚Äôt already done it, the best thing would be to start off with an apology. 
Let them know you understand how you hurt them and that you are genuinely sorry. If they don‚Äôt accept your apology or refuse to talk to you, you will have to respect that and give them their space. If they do forgive you then I suggest you take things slow and try to rebuild their trust in you. 
Be kind towards them, like you would to your friends. When they start responding positively, you can ask them if they want to hang out.ü§ó If you have the same friends, you could hang out as a group ‚Äì this can help them feel more comfortable. But don‚Äôt force it ‚Äì let it happen naturally.

Long distance relationships - should I try?
-----------------------------
"Can long distance relationship really work?"
 -----------------------------
Yes, it can work. Long distance relationships can sometimes need more work from both partners. Some people find it hard to date a person that they won‚Äôt see whenever they want to. But if two people are serious about each other, distance won‚Äôt get in the way.üòä
These days distance isn‚Äôt the problem it was in the past. Now we have things like cellphones and WhatsApp. This means your partner is a phone-call, text or video call away. So even if you aren‚Äôt physically together, there are still other ways to chat whenever you want to.
Like any other relationship, a long distance relationship can work so long as two people care for each other and communicate their feelings. But you might need to be more creative on how you show your partner love and when you do get to spend time together, make those moments extra special üíñ

Can I get pregnant through oral sex?
-----------------------------
"Can I get pregnant by sucking a guy's penis?"
 -----------------------------
Oral sex, such as sucking a guy‚Äôs penis won‚Äôt get you pregnant. Pregnancy happens through vaginal sex or if his sperm finds a way inside your vagina while you're having foreplay.
When sperm comes in contact with a vagina, there's a chance it will travel to your uterus and come in contact with your eggs. And when the two meet, fertilization can happen and that's how a pregnancy starts. But this can't happen from sucking his penis. Even if you swallow his sperm during oral sex, you aren't at risk of pregnancy. 
But sucking a guy's penis isn't completely safe, it can carry risk of STIs such as herpes, gonorrhoea, syphilis and HIV. To practice safe oral sex, I'd suggest you use a condom during oral sex to reduce risk of transmission.

Does he like you? 
-----------------------------
"How do I know if a guy likes me"
 -----------------------------
There isn‚Äôt a standard way to tell if someone likes you. Everyone is different; some are shy and some are really out there with their feelings. This means that people behave and communicate in different ways. Who knew it... crushes and love ain't easy! üòâ Generally you can get the vibe from the things they do. For example, they cheer you up when you're sad or help you out with problems.
It's likely they'll also want to spend time with you. Maybe they'll ask you to hang out with them over the weekends or they'll always want to walk with you to and from school. If you notice that they're going out of their way to chill with you, then it‚Äôs possible they like you. 
But, all of these things can also mean that person is just into being your friend too. The best way to figure out if someone is into you is to... ask them! I know it seems scary, but if you're into them too... it could be cool to talk about it üòÑ

Remember, just because someone is showing they like you and do nice things for you, it doesn't mean you have to like them back. It's important to go at your own pace and respond when it's comfortable with you. You decide if and when you're ready üòä

Ouch! Sex hurts 
-----------------------------
"Having sex with my boyfriend hurt, what can I do to ease the pain?"
 -----------------------------
Ouch. Pain during sex is not cool! üò¨. Some discomfort can be normal, but pain is a no-no. Let me run you through this in more detail. Since the vagina is a muscle, it can become tense if you're not totally feeling like having sex or if you're nervous before or during sex.
If you're feeling some discomfort, you should take a break. When you feel ready, you can spend more time on foreplay; kissing and touching. This can help you to get more aroused and wet down there and also lead to more enjoyable sex for you. You can slow down, try different positions and most importantly - use lubricant! This can be bought at a pharmacy or clinic. Remember to use water-based lube as it doesn't damage condoms.
If you feel pain during sex, you should always stop. Sex shouldn't hurt and it's ok to stop and prioritise your wellbeing. If you're having pain during any type of sex that doesn't go away, visit your doctor or a health centre and they can best support you üè•

Sex is never something that you should be pressured into doing and both people should want to do it and agree to it. Think ü§îabout how you feel and only have sex when you are truly ready.     
You have the right to be unsure. If your partner is threatening you by saying you don't love them, this is not a good sign üõë. When you make the decision to have sex, make sure that it is because it feels right, not because you feel bad or guilty. Speak to a trusted adult or call Love Life at 011 523 1000 for more guidance.

If it's my first time can I get pregnant?
-----------------------------
"Hi Big Sis. I am a virgin, if I have sex once without the use of condoms,will I get pregnant?"
 -----------------------------
Great question! If you have started menstruating (have periods) and don't use contraception, the chance of getting pregnant are high. Menstruation is the body's way of telling you that it is able to have a baby. Every month, an egg is released from the ovaries, which if left unfertilised, will flush away with a girl's usual monthly period.
These tiny eggs can be fertilised when sperm from a penis swims up the vagina and meets it in a uterus (womb). Fertilisation can happen via unprotected sexual activity between a penis and a vagina. Remember, there is a risk of pregnancy not just during sex but during foreplay too. If you want to enjoy sex but avoid pregnancy, the best option is to use a condom and another form of contraception such as the pill, IUD or injection. 
Anytime you engage in sexual activity with someone, have sex, it's always best to use a condom in order to avoid an unwanted pregnancy or STIs. Contraceptives help you enjoy sex safely. If you have any more questions contact Love Life Sexual Health line 0800 121 900 toll-free.

 -----------------------------
Menstrual pain can really make it difficult for us to move around and do simple things around the house or even go to school üò£. There are a few things you can do. Light exercise can help to reduce the pain. You can also try putting a hot water bottle against the lower part of your tummy, to reduce pain.

If none if the above options work then I‚Äôd really advise you to go and get yourself checked out by a doctor. Sometimes menstrual pain can be a sign of a more serious issue that needs medical attention. I'm sure you're fine but just get checked to be on the safe side ü§ó

Unprotected sex when you have an implant 
-----------------------------
"Can I fall pregnant if I have unprotected sex and he cums inside of me while I have an implant"
 -----------------------------
There is a chance that you will get pregnant but it is a very small chance. An implant gives 99% protection from pregnancy. It releases a hormone into your body called progestin. This hormone blocks your eggs from coming out your ovaries and also thickens your uterus to stop sperm from entering. 
The risk of pregnancy also comes when the implant has reached its expiration date and you haven‚Äôt removed it. Usually, an implant should last between 2 or 3 years. After that time you will need to remove  it and get a new one. Make sure you keep track! ‚è∞
The new implant will start working after 7 days. During this time, you will need to use a condom for protection. To check if your implant has expired, visit the nurse or doctor who gave you the procedure. An implant only protects from pregnancy so always use a condom for STI/HIV protection.
